            <entry xml:id="entry_æna" xml:lang="os">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>æna</orth></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>мама</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>mama</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>матушка</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>mother</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>бабушка</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>granny</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">детское и
                        почтительно-ласковое название для матери, бабки: </note><note type="comment"
                        xml:lang="en">childish or honorific/diminutive name for mother, grandmother:
                    </note></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>ox, æna, ci kænon!</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>о, мать, что мне делать!</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>oh mother, what should I do!</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>22</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>æna xæbīzǵyn k˳y skodta...</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>когда матушка приготовила пирог с сыром...</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>when mother made a cheese pie...</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОТ"/><biblScope>96</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>ūs yn zaǧta; ænajy nom myl k˳y næ sæværdtais, wæd dæ
                            axordtain</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>женщина ему сказала: если бы ты не назвал меня %sæna%s, я бы тебя
                                съела</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the woman told him: if you had not called me %sæna%s, I would have
                                eaten you</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>82</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>ana</w>
                        <gloss><q>мать</q></gloss></mentioned>. Распространено в кавказских языках:
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/>
                        <w>an</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kbd-x-crc"><lang/>
                        <w>anne</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/>
                        <w>hane</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/>
                        <w>na</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>na</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="dar"><lang/>
                        <w>ana</w>
                        <gloss><q>мать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="dar"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>бабушка</q></gloss></mentioned>. Ср. также <mentioned
                        xml:lang="hit"><lang/>
                        <w>anna</w>
                        <gloss><q>мать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>anna</w>
                        <gloss><q>кормилица</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>ἀννίς</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="goh"><lang/>
                        <w>ana</w>
                        <gloss><q>бабушка</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="prg"><lang/>
                        <w>ane</w>
                        <gloss><q>старая мать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>ana</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="hu"><lang/>
                        <w>anja</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kca" dialect="kca"><lang/>
                        <w>ana</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="udm"><lang/>
                        <w>anaj</w>
                        <gloss><q>мать</q></gloss></mentioned> и др. „Детское“ слово. Симметричный
                    термин для ‘отца’ — <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æda"/> q. v. См. также <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_nana"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_dada"
                    />.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Compare with <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>ana</w>
                        <gloss><q>mother</q></gloss></mentioned>. Widespread in Caucasian languages:
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/>
                        <w>an</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kbd-x-crc"><lang/>
                        <w>anne</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/>
                        <w>hane</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/>
                        <w>na</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>na</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="dar"><lang/>
                        <w>ana</w>
                        <gloss><q>mother</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="dar"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>grandmother</q></gloss></mentioned>. Consider also <mentioned
                        xml:lang="hit"><lang/>
                        <w>anna</w>
                        <gloss><q>mother</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>anna</w>
                        <gloss><q>foster-mother</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>ἀννίς</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="goh"><lang/>
                        <w>ana</w>
                        <gloss><q>grandmother</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="prg"><lang/>
                        <w>ane</w>
                        <gloss><q>old mother</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>ana</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="hu"><lang/>
                        <w>anja</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kca" dialect="kca"><lang/>
                        <w>ana</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="udm"><lang/>
                        <w>anaj</w>
                        <gloss><q>mother</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. “Children's” language word.
                    Symmetrical term for ‘father’ is <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æda"/> q. v. See
                    also <ref type="xr" target="#entry_nana"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_dada"
                    />.</etym>
            </entry>
